{"overview":"This C-minor sonata movement displays a textbook yet dramatically charged sonata form, with a recurring Grave introduction that punctuates the Allegro at structurally pivotal moments—development, coda—functioning as a rhetorical 'fate' interpolation unique to this design. The harmonic language is notably taut, driven by dense diminished-seventh chains in the Grave, a striking chromatic-mediant plunge to E major at the development's outset, and a luminous modal mixture shift to C major for the recapitulated second theme before the inevitable collapse back to C minor.","cross_piece_tags":["sonata_form","chromatic_mediant","modal_mixture","dramatic","tragic","arpeggiated_bass","counterpoint","circle_of_fifths"]}
